## Background 
    …

## Ingredients

- 1.25 kg ground pork
- 3-4 guajillo peppers (30g)
- 1 chile ancho (10g)
- 1-2 chile de arbol (optional - a spicy pepper)
- 4 cloves
- 1 small onion 
- 10 black peppercorns
- 2 large cloves of garlic
- 1 tsp chicken stock powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1/2 tsp oregano
-  ¼ tsp thyme
- ¼ tsp cumin
- ½ tsp paprika
- 1 pinch of ground ginger
- ½ cup (white or apple) vinegar

 


## Directions

1. Remove seeds from pepper
2. Boil the peppers at a high heat, with enough water to partial cover them for 5 minutes
3. Allow peppers to cool down
4. Blend all ingredients minus the pork
5. Add water that peppers soaked in as needed, to reach desired consistency. Although you want the sauce to be thick and dense.
6. Mix meat with sauce, let rest a couple hours or overnight. 
7. Cook
